data.text:
Also, special shout out to Bully.

The gay strip teases were EVERYTHING

https://t.co/5kj5Y7E8UN

I was super into WWF/WWE when I was younger. I even went to see it live in Berlin.

And if you weren't in love with Randy Orton back in 2002, you probably weren't Gay. https://t.co/IhQyQMVCXN

I will never forget staying up until 3/4 in the morning to watch Queer As Folk on Canal +.

The poor signal making the screen fuzzy and seeing Justin discover himself. Heaven. https://t.co/098sjwbxx1

To this day I know the majority of Green Day songs, word for word.

Billie Joe Armstrong is one of the most beautiful men to ever live. https://t.co/0FvMfC4BnU

I was also a 'troubled' kid. So Pete Doherty, and The Libertines, had a special place in my heart.

His mum also happened to be my school nurse. https://t.co/XAZDvO6Rns
Brad Pitt in Fight Club was a 'coming of age' moment for me. https://t.co/lEM5TBsmLq
